name: long-chain-fatty-acid---CoA ligase
names: long-chain fatty acyl coenzyme A synthetase
reaction: ATP + a long-chain fatty acid + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + an acyl-CoA [RN:R00390]
comment: Acts on a wide range of long-chain saturated and unsaturated fatty acids, but the enzymes from different tissues show some variation in specificity. The liver enzyme acts on acids from C6 to C20; that from brain shows high activity up to C24.

orthologs.K08746: solute carrier family 27 (fatty acid transporter), member 2
